bcl:definition.bcl:text:
extraprovincial corporation means an extraprovincial credit union or an
extraprovincial trust corporation authorized to carry on deposit business, whose primary
jurisdiction is not Canada or a province designated under section 158 (5) of the Act;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
in the case of a credit union authorized to carry on deposit business, or an
          extraprovincial corporation, a requirement that at least a specified percentage of its
          total assets be held in low-risk investments;

the powers and duties of any committees or officers to whom the power to make
          investments or loans is delegated from the directors and any conditions to which the
          delegations are subject;
